parameters: Yo, I came about the wolf matter.

Shopkeeper Tag: Oh, if Simos' husband is here, then we have
the strength of a hundred men!

Simos from the Night of Ignorance: This is the territory of
the Goats, right? Did that mercenary captain run away from
the wolves?

Shopkeeper Tag: It seems like they're busy, the members of
the Bulk Gang have been in a frenzy for a while now.

Shopkeeper Tag: We are the receptacle for troubles around
here. We are a long-standing organization that existed even
before the Empire annexed Wald.

Shopkeeper Tag: Without their permission, we can't take any
requests around here. Actually, it's also forbidden to
outsource the requests to outsiders. Keep it a secret, okay?

Simos from the Night of Ignorance: So, where is the wolf
pack?

Shopkeeper Tag: It's in the forest cave. The livestock has
been suffering from damage, so please take care of it as
soon as possible.

Simos from the Night of Ignorance: Alright, come and
exterminate every last one of the wolves to test your
strength.

Simos from the Night of Ignorance: After checking if there
are any leftovers from the hunt, I'll go too, old man. Bring
me the strongest drink here.
Shopkeeper Tag: Please wait a moment.

Shopkeeper Tag: That was a close one! Adventurers come in
all sorts, I tell ya.

Shopkeeper Tag: If it's you guys, you might even earn the
recognition of the Goat Lord.
Clea: Goat... One of the leaders of the pioneer children.

Shopkeeper Tag: That's right, around here the Goat is known
as the captain of the mercenary corps of the Bulk Gang.

Shopkeeper Tag: If you have the chance, you should meet him.
Well then, I'll make sure to properly pay you the reward.
Shimosu of the Unknown Night: Hurry up and come back!

Shopkeeper Tag: Welcome, guests of the Empire. I hope you
find something that suits your taste.
Shopkeeper Tag: Please hurry up, okay?

Shopkeeper Tag: Thanks for your help, as expected of the
Adventurer's Guild!

Innkeeper: Oh, a new face? It may not be much, but feel free
to relax here.

Drunk customer: Imperial people don't drink beer, so how do
they regain their daily energy?

Traveling weapons merchant: 'I'm originally from Oros, but
now I'm captivated by this beer... ku~!'

Female Bard: How about a song about the heroes of Vald? The
warriors who bravely fought against the empire are still
beloved to this day.
